  "body": "If I make a transaction call and the last argument I pass is null, the code throws an error. I found that this code is to blame (line 140 in contract.js as of current revision):\r\n\r\n```\r\nsynchronizeFunction: function(fn, instance, C) {\r\n      var self = this;\r\n      return function() {\r\n        var args = Array.prototype.slice.call(arguments);\r\n        var tx_params = {};\r\n        var last_arg = args[args.length - 1];\r\n\r\n        // It's only tx_params if it's an object and not a BigNumber.\r\n        if (Utils.is_object(last_arg) && !Utils.is_big_number(last_arg)) {\r\n          tx_params = args.pop();\r\n        }\r\n```\r\n\r\n`Utils.is_object()` returns `true` for `null` values, so it's assumed to be an object and later on is attempted to get parsed for settings (like `from`, `value` etc.) and throws `TypeError: Cannot convert undefined or null to object`\r\n\r\nThere should be a check for `null` value either inside `Util.is_object()` or here on the line `if (Utils.is_object(last_arg) && !Utils.is_big_number(last_arg)) {`. \r\n\r\nThis line should be this instead: \r\n\r\n`if (lastArg && Utils.is_object(last_arg) && !Utils.is_big_number(last_arg)) {`\r\n\r\n",
